<li>Engineers have a responsibility to act in the best interests of public safety, even if it means sacrificing other priorities such as cost or schedule.</li> 
      <li>Engineers must be transparent and honest about potential safety hazards associated with their work.
All relevant stakeholders must be informed about these risks.</li>
<li>Ethical considerations are important in safety and risk management.</li>



